parameters: This scene will be ready in one of the next builds!\.\. Thank you for playing up to this point!
To every citizen of our beloved End City.
The Self Defense Committee thanks you for the goods you're willing to part from.\.\. Cash \G will be emitted by this Mana powered Offering Box in exchange for your items.
Thank you for using this Offering Box!
\n<End City Farmer>Ya...\.\.\. don't look like you've ever work'd th' land,\. kitten.
\n<End City Farmer>I can give you some tool we're done usin',\. but...\.\.\. th' hoe don' make th' farmer!
\n<End City Farmer>Heave-oh!\.\. It's hard work,\. but my boy is down in the Hole,\. gotta make sure he gets fresh crops regularly!
\n<\n[1]>You're a big,\. dumb,\. boy.\.\. You know that?\.\. Don't act so friendly,\. people will make use of it...

"To the Spring Goddess,\. blessing End City with clean water and bountiful crops."
"May she watch over our youth and deliver them swiftly to safety."
\n<Ferry Granny>Oh dear,\. you want to cross the river?
\n<Ferry Granny>It will be 10\g,\. sweetie~\.\. For THAT THING,\. you know,\. right?
\n<Ferry Granny>{O' SPRING GODDESS!\.\. NURTURING US AND OUR YOUNG BRAVES IN THE HOLE!}
\n<Ferry Granny>{FORGIVE THIS YOUNG SOUL FOR DEFILING YOUR SHORES!\.\. HERE'S OUR OFFERING FOR YOU!!}
The granny grabs the \G you've paid for the ride and...\.\.\.
\n<Ferry Granny>No \G,\. dear?\.\. The Spring Goddess will be waiting for your offering~
\n<Ferry Granny>The Lake let us through,\. once again~
\n<\n[1]>You're not too good at faking what you feel,\. Shina.\.\. It's no good pretending the elephant in the room ain't there.\.\.
Shina lets out a sigh,\. not expecting to be cornered so easily.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Do you at least have any news about him?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Nope,\. nothing yet,\. but he's probably not too deep in shit.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>He's gotta be fine.\.\. Kid knows how to look out for himself.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Well,\. with you as his big sister,\. I'm sure that's the case,\. right?\.\.
\n<\n[4]>You seem to be handling the stress a lot better than I am...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Stress?\.\. I'm not stressed,\. like I said,\. the brat'll find his way back home.\.\. I'm pissed.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Who the hell do those bastards think they are?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>They think they can just walk in here and snatch up my brother?!\.\. They can't steal other people's stuff like that!\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Yeah...\.\.\.they really are just a group of bullies and thugs.\.\. Still,\. I can't help but worry about him...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Well,\. not much I can do to help you there,\. can I?\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Sorry to be such a downer,\. I'm sure he's fine like you said.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Yeah,\. yeah,\. don't mention it.\.\. Watch,\. he'll probably be back before sundown.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Well,\. so much for him showing up by sundown,\. huh.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Eh,\. he's fine.\.\. I know it,\. he has to be.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I'm gonna head out,\. see ya later Shina.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Well,\. I'm really tired from work,\. so I was thinking maybe we could spend some time relaxing together.\.\.
\^\n<\n[4]>You know...\.\.\. we could just go to the Nekofish Bathouse and just relax in there for a little,\. like we used to back in the-\.\.\. \BST[2]!\.\.
Shina cuts herself off mid sentence,\. regretting her choice of words.\.\. She lets out a sigh before reluctantly finishing her sentence.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>...It won't be the same without him, will it?
\n<\n[4]>I'm...I'm sorry Neko, I really shouldn't have said that.
\n<\n[4]>I'm so clumsy with my words, I'm really sorry.
\n<\n[1]>Whatever, it is what it is. Just forget about it.
